<topic id="gemstone" revisionNumber="1">
  <developerConceptualDocument xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
    <introduction>
      <para>
        The 
        <externalLink>
          <linkText>Grid Protection Alliance</linkText>
          <linkAlternateText>Grid Protection Alliance</linkAlternateText>
          <linkUri>https://gridprotectionalliance.org/</linkUri>
          <linkTarget>_blank</linkTarget>
        </externalLink>        
        Gemstone Expressions Library is a useful collection of open source classes and methods for expressions and expression parsing.
      </para>
    </introduction>
    <section>
      <title>About the Gemstone Library</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          The Grid Protection Alliance Gemstone Library is a collection of handy open source .NET code assemblies based on
          <externalLink>
            <linkText>continuous development since 2004.</linkText>
            <linkAlternateText>Grid Solutions Framework Contributions</linkAlternateText>
            <linkUri>https://github.com/GridProtectionAlliance/gsf/graphs/contributors</linkUri>
            <linkTarget>_blank</linkTarget>
          </externalLink>.
        </para>
        <para>
          These packages represent a focused re-envisioning of the best libraries, i.e., the "gems", from the
          <externalLink>
            <linkText>Grid Solutions Framework</linkText>
            <linkAlternateText>Grid Solutions Framework</linkAlternateText>
            <linkUri>https://github.com/GridProtectionAlliance/gsf/</linkUri>
            <linkTarget>_blank</linkTarget>
          </externalLink>
          (GSF), which has long been in use by various open source projects and electric power utilities worldwide.
        </para>
        <para>
          The Gemstone Library contains a large variety of code useful for any .NET project with of hundreds of class libraries that extend or expand the functionality included in .NET,
          including many tools and protocol parsers that are useful for the electric power industry. For example:
        </para>
        <list class="bullet">
          <listItem>
            <para>
              <legacyBold>
                <externalLink>
                  <linkText>gemstone.threading</linkText>
                  <linkAlternateText>gemstone.threading</linkAlternateText>
                  <linkUri>https://gemstone.github.io/threading/</linkUri>
                  <linkTarget>_blank</linkTarget>
                </externalLink>               
              </legacyBold>
              The Gemstone Threading Library organizes all Gemstone functionality related to threading.
            </para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>
              <legacyBold>
                <externalLink>
                  <linkText>gemstone.expressions</linkText>
                  <linkAlternateText>gemstone.expressions</linkAlternateText>
                  <linkUri>https://gemstone.github.io/expressions/</linkUri>
                  <linkTarget>_blank</linkTarget>
                </externalLink>
              </legacyBold>
              The Gemstone Expressions Library organizes all Gemstone functionality related to expression parsing.
            </para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
      </content>
    </section>
  </developerConceptualDocument>
</topic>
